==English==

===Etymology===
From the Middle English ''coppeweb''.  From ''coppe'' (''spider''), from ''attercoppe'', from Old English ''āttercoppe'', from ''ātor'' (''poison'') + ''copp'' (''head''); + ''web'' (''web'').

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# a [[spider]]’s [[web]], or the [[remain]]s of one
# one of its [[filament]]s; [[gossamer]]
# an [[intricate]] [[plot]]
#{{computing}} a [[web page]] that either has not been [[update]]d for a long time, or that is rarely [[visit]]ed

